<h2>Geocaches</h2>
<h3><a name="Geocaches">What is a geocache?</a></h3>
<p>
A geocache is container which has been hidden. It often contains at least a log book, to note your visit in, and perhaps other items, like toys, for swapping. They can be found using GPS coordinates which mark to its location. 
</p>
<h3><a name="HowDoIFindAGeocache">How do I find a geocache?</a></h3>
<p>Typically a GPS device is used to find the device, but a map could be used. On GeoArmy, use your android phone and geoArmy app to search for a cache you wish to find, then simple let your phone guide you to the location. Once there, you may need to search a bit to find the cache.</p>
<h3><a name="HowDoIUploadAGeocache">How do I upload a geocache?</a></h3>
<p>To upload a geocache, first hide your cache and note the coordinates using a GPS device, then log in to the site. Click "Manage my GeoCaches", then "Upload GeoCache". Enter the details, and click "Update".</p>
